article.headline: UAB 78, UTEP 73
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- Robert Vaden scored 21 points and Howard Crawford added a career-high 19 to lead Alabama-Birmingham to a 78-73 Conference USA victory over Texas-El Paso on Wednesday night. Channing Toney scored 17 points and Paul Delaney III had 11 for UAB (12-7, 2-2). Randy Culpepper scored 26 points and Stefon Jackson added 24 for UTEP (11-7, 2-2). Aaron Johnson had eight points and five rebounds for UAB, with most of his production coming in the clutch. A 3-pointer by Tavaris Watts gave UTEP a 53-52 lead with 8:00 left in the game. But Johnson hit back-to-back runners in the lane to put UAB on top 56-53, and the Blazers led the rest of the way. UTEP pulled to within three points twice in the final 30 seconds. But Toney and Crawford hit two free throws apiece to keep UAB in front.
